Soher Made Our Night Unforgettable – Ask for Him!
Oct 2024 • Couples
So, my wife Hania and I came to Cloud 22 at the Royal Atlantis to celebrate her 30th birthday. We booked a session from 7 to 10 pm, and wow, what a night! A huge part of that was thanks to Soher, our waiter, who made the whole experience next level.

From the moment we stepped in, Soher greeted us like we were old friends – super warm, always smiling, and ready to help. Now, here’s the funny part: we couldn’t make up our minds on where to sit and changed our seats a couple of times (don’t ask!). But Soher? Not once did he lose his cool. He was still smiling, happy, and genuinely enjoying helping us settle in. It was like he was in on our back-and-forth decision-making.

The real surprise? Soher sang for my wife and trust me, it wasn’t just your regular happy birthday song. It was like we got our own private concert, and honestly, that alone made the night unforgettable. It was such a sweet, genuine moment that had us both smiling ear to ear.

And as if that wasn’t enough, he even offered to take pictures of us by the infinity pool capturing that perfect Dubai skyline shot. He’s not just a great waiter; the guy's a photographer too! Bonus points for that!

When it came to food, Soher knew exactly what to recommend, as if he had a sixth sense about our taste buds. Everything he suggested was absolutely on point – we loved every bite!

By the end of the night, I was already texting my friends, telling them they have to come to Cloud 22, and when they do, to ask for Soher specifically. He didn’t just make the night special – he made us feel like VIPs, all while being fun and personable.

So, if you’re reading this, do yourself a favor: go to Cloud 22 and ask for Soher. He’s got a gift for turning a good evening into a great one. Thank you, Soher, for making my wife’s birthday something we’ll talk about for years!

To Soher's manager: you are incredibly lucky to have someone like him on your team. His warmth, attention to detail, and ability to connect with guests make him a true asset. We’ll definitely be back, and a big part of that is because of the fantastic experience Soher gave us!
Written October 17, 2024
